# Noetfield — No vendor names on buyer surfaces

## Policy (locked)

- **Never** name third-party companies on public www, GTM copy, MSP/federal hubs, investor pages, or active ops/agent docs.
- **Never** write comparison pages, battlecards, scorecards, vendor tables, or “not another X” / “they configure; we …” framing on www.
- Use **buyer patterns only**: receipt-first, trust center, procurement ZIP, Phase 1/2 MSP, numbered narrative, honest scope badges.
- If copy does not help a buyer decide or pay, remove it. Do not overshare internal systems architecture.

## Allowed

- **Microsoft** product/docs names when factual (Purview, Copilot Control System, M365, Entra, Learn links).
- **Government** sources (Canada.ca AIA, TBS ADM, NIST AI RMF).
- **TrustField Technologies** as invoicing entity where already locked.

## Verify

Run before demo or www ship:

```bash
make verify-no-vendor-names
```

Fix generator (`scripts/rebuild-www-v6.py`) and regenerate HTML — do not hand-patch vendor strings into static pages.

## Forbidden in new work

- `/compare/` routes, battlecard docs, competitor tables, “category scorecards”
- Vendor names in `success_reference`, homepage copy, MSP hero, investor zone map
- Analyst firm name-drops used as social proof
